task_description: Facing the building to your North-East (approx. 50°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to estimate the height of the building directly in front of me; looking up will help me see the full vertical extent from ground to roof.
I am currently looking up at the building but need to adjust my pitch further to capture the full height from base to roof for accurate estimation.
I am still not seeing the full vertical extent of the building; I need to look further up to capture the roofline and estimate height accurately.
I have already tilted up multiple times and may be at or near the maximum pitch; now I need to look down to locate the base of the building for height estimation.
I am now looking too far down and have lost sight of the building; I need to look up slightly to reacquire the base and roofline for height estimation.
I have a partial view of the building’s facade; to estimate height accurately, I need to see both the base and roof — I’ll look down slightly to locate the ground level.
I can now see the base of the building; I will look up to capture the roofline and estimate total height based on visual proportion and known reference points.
I have a clear view of the building’s roofline and base from prior adjustments; based on visual scaling and typical floor heights, I estimate the building is approximately 24 meters tall.
